      "generationGuide": {
        "action": "How to Generate",
        "title": "How to generate sprites",
        "description": "Conversation is for generating images through chat. Code is for generating images through Vibe Coding.",
        "tabs": {
          "conversation": "Conversation",
          "code": "Code"
        },
        "clipboardAction": "Copy",
        "clipboardSucceeded": "Generation guide copied",
        "clipboardFailed": "Copy failed",
        "prompts": {
          "conversation": "# 下蛋 sprite sheet prompt\n\nGenerate an import-ready 8×8 PNG sprite sheet for 下蛋. The character is: [describe the character identity, outfit, and visual style here]. Keep the same identity, body type, outfit, proportions, and art style across every frame.\n\nOutput requirements:\n- The canvas must be square: 8 rows × 8 columns, 64 frames total, with exactly equal cell sizes and pixel-aligned boundaries.\n- Do not draw grid lines, borders, frame numbers, text labels, watermarks, headings, or extra decorations.\n- Each frame contains only the same character, centered with enough safe padding. Do not crop the character and do not add shadows.\n- Prefer a transparent background. If the model cannot reliably output transparency, use a solid pure magenta #ff00ff background so it can be keyed out later.\n- Output only the sprite sheet PNG, not a poster or explanatory image.\n\nRows from top to bottom:\n1. Greeting: friendly greeting, light wave or nod, loopable.\n2. Snoring: sleeping or dozing; closed-eye breathing and slight body rise/fall, no yawning.\n3. Upset: one stable negative emotion such as annoyed, sad, shocked, or angry.\n4. Celebrate: excited celebration with clear rhythmic motion.\n5. Seeking: confused searching, looking around, or trying to find something.\n6. Embarrassed: shy or awkward motion, restrained and cute.\n7. Working: one work mode such as writing, computer work, or crafting; do not mix modes.\n8. ListeningToMusic: immersed listening, light swaying, nodding, and rhythm.\n\nMotion requirements: each row is one looped behavior, and the 8 frames must have continuous but visible differences. Do not use mirrored filler frames or near-duplicates. If the model supports a staged conversation, first provide the 64-frame motion plan, then generate the final PNG after confirmation.",
          "code": "# 下蛋 sprite code-generation task\n\nGoal: use an image model to generate 64 separate square frames, then stitch them locally into an import-ready sprite.png. Do not ask the image model to draw the final 8×8 sheet directly, because generated grids are often not pixel-aligned.\n\nFinal specification:\n- Recommended sprite.png: 4096×4096 PNG, 8×8 grid, each cell 512×512.\n- 下蛋 accepts square 8×8 PNG sheets from 1024×1024 to 5120×5120.\n- Fixed row order: Greeting, Snoring, Upset, Celebrate, Seeking, Embarrassed, Working, ListeningToMusic.\n\nWorkflow:\n1. Write a 64-frame plan first: 8 frames per row, preserving one character identity, outfit, body type, and style.\n2. Generate each frame as an isolated square image, named row01_col01.png through row08_col08.png.\n3. Prefer transparent backgrounds. If the model cannot output transparency, use a flat pure magenta #ff00ff background. No shadows, borders, grids, or text.\n4. Post-process every frame locally: convert #ff00ff to alpha; find the visible-pixel bounding box; scale with one consistent scale per row; center inside a 512×512 transparent cell with at least 40px safe margin.\n5. Stitch the normalized frames in row-major order into an 8×8 4096×4096 sheet and save it as sprite.png.\n6. Validate the final file: square; within 1024×1024 to 5120×5120; width and height divisible by 8; all 64 cells contain visible pixels; adjacent frames have continuous motion and no duplicate filler.\n\nBehavior definitions:\n- Greeting: friendly greeting, light wave or nod, loopable.\n- Snoring: sleeping or dozing with only closed-eye breathing and body rise/fall.\n- Upset: one stable negative emotion.\n- Celebrate: excited celebration with clear rhythm.\n- Seeking: confused searching or looking around.\n- Embarrassed: shy or awkward restrained motion.\n- Working: one work mode only; do not mix modes.\n- ListeningToMusic: immersed listening, light swaying and nodding.\n\nDeliverable: output sprite.png."
        }
      },
